As far as instruments, Space Designer and the EXS24 suffer without, specifically, the logic studio additional content disk. The warped effects for Space Designer and the Samples for the Xtreme synthesizer instruments for EXS24 are contained on that disk. Otherwise you are getting every new feature in Logic 9, excluding any new sounds (i.e. voices) that may come from the Jam Pack disks. I'm sure all the disks will end up around here soon though.

hey donshanto, this is not the full install, just the programs, so you have to uncheck everything that isn't on the first disk. You will still be able to use all the new feature minus a few things with EXS24 and Space Designer, but they are minor. The best way to know that you are only installing what's on the first disk is to uncheck things until the installer says that does not give you that message that you will need another disk during the install. If you get no message, you are good. Once the full torrent can be put up and/or you decide to buy it, you won't have to do that.

Here is the error specificly: Dyld Error Message:
  Library not loaded: /Library/Frameworks/XSKey.framework/Versions/A/XSKey
  Referenced from: /Applications/Logic Pro.app/Contents/MacOS/Logic Pro

Ok i found a solution. Since I still had my logic studio 8, i opened it's contents and found the xskey, pasted it in the library, and it worked! I doubt anyone else will have that problem, but just in case that's how i fixed it.

How to install, and update to 9.1:

1. Install Logic and all the content you have available.
Use this serial:
E-330-DOX-030-NJB-265-AKZ-414-BVZ-M2E-41HX

2. Update everything EXCEPT - Logic 2.1 and Mainstage 2.0.1.
Use this serial when starting Logic:
E-342-PXV-169-TMH-378-IKJ-435-KXZ-FFS-41PX

3. Update the rest.

Instructions (Really Easy) ------

1. Download it

2. Install it. It'll ask you to have some discs ready but just ignore it, and at the end if it asks you for the discs just click cancel. It'll say install failed but it will have installed correctly! After this do not open Logic yet.

3. Download the torrent provided by hezatuz ( http://www.mac-torrents.com/torrents.php?mode=details&id=ecf0f896f88498a944a677f7c131723b7472e9b6 )

4. Extract the 2 rar files by clicking one of them and using something like Zipeg for extraction.

5. Install the .dmg file you just extracted.

6. After that, still don't open Logic. You'll notice two other files in that folder you extracted. Select them then press CMD + C. Go to your hard drive, then Library/Application Support/ProApps.

7. You'll notice in this folder there will be two files named the same. What you need to do is replace them two files to remove the licensing. Press CMD + V to paste the two original files from the extracted rar into the ProApps folder.

8. Done :)
